4307.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4307.description: To impress his fan club, Po releases the Mongolian Fist Demon. Now he has to figure out how to defeat the Demon and save the village and his fans!

4308.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4308.description: Po disobeys Shifu's orders and looks into the Mystical Mirror of Yin and Yang, creating two versions of himself: one good and one evil!

4332.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4332.description: After dealing Taotie yet another humiliating defeat, Po is horrified to learn that the villainous warthog has had a full on nervous breakdown. Po is determined to heal his spirit and Taotie is eager to change his evil ways...or is he?

4333.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4333.description: When Po's fake love letter prank on Monkey backfires, the duo's relationship is put to the test in a story of jealousy, betrayal and, yes, even kidnapping.

4339.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4339.description: When Temutai kidnaps a kung fu master, Shifu turns to Po for help.

4340.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4340.description: Po discovers his dad, Mr. Ping, is dating Scorpion, but he has trouble trusting his former enemy who claims to no longer be evil.

4348.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4348.description: Po realizes he must select a trophy for the Hall of Heroes, but instead finds himself helping a young villager retrieve a rabbit doll that is much more important than it looks.

4349.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4349.description: Po disguises himself as the merciless villain, Tong Fo, to try and locate a hidden weapon.

4359.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4359.description: When Taotie tries to destroy the Jade Palace and fails, he is sent to prison while his son, Bian Zao, is left behind with Po, who acts like a big brother to the boy who thinks everything is lame!

4360.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4360.description: While repairs are being made to the noodle shop, Mr. Ping turns the training hall into a restaurant!

10405.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10405.description: When Shifu's con-man father comes back into town, Po finds himself in the middle.

10406.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10406.description: Po is excited when he discovers a kung fu prodigy, but starts to worry when people seem to prefer the new kid to their beloved Dragon Warrior.

10430.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10430.description: Po is distraught when he learns that everyone in town has been invited to a fancy dinner party except for him, due to his slovenly behavior and table manners. Will Shifu and the Five be able to teach Po proper etiquette AND foil the attack of evil Temutai and his army? Not likely.

10431.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10431.description: When Shifu's ex-girlfriend, Mei Ling, visits the Jade Palace, Po decides to try and get them back together, despite the fact Mei Ling is now Shifu's most hated enemy.

10437.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10437.description: Po befriends a band of dancers, unaware they're actually a band of traveling thieves.

10438.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10438.description: When the Furious 5 are all out of town and the Jade Palace is attacked, Po only has his dad and two old people to help him.

10446.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10446.description: A rash of thefts in the Valley of Peace has the villagers in uproar and things only get worse when the culprit appears to be... Monkey?

10447.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10447.description: Po's Kung Fu hero, Kwan the Unkillable, comes to the Valley of Peace and appears to be a feeble old man. Po agrees to stage a fight to help him get back on top. But Kwan may not be as weak as he looks.

10457.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10457.description: Master Chao visits the valley to oversee a Tournament. Shifu is convinced that Po and Master Chao want to replace him. Shifu's old enemy, Pai Mei, arrives in the middle of the tournament and threatens to destroy Shifu.

10458.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
10458.description: Master Yao returns to the Jade Palace and announces that he's offering the Valley of Peace a one-day 'Wonder and Wisdom Exchange'. Anyone who brings him a new wonder will be allowed to ask him a single question.

16958.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16958.description: Po saves a girl from some bandits, only to learn that she's engaged to be married to the Dragon Warrior.

16959.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16959.description: During a fight with Tong Fo, Po is struck by lightning, giving him the power to read minds.

16983.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16983.description: Po and Tigress must track down and stop a messenger from delivering a scroll that could thrust China into all-out war!

16984.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16984.description: Po and the Furious Five meet their greatest challenge yet: a supernatural creature who is invincible to the powers of kung fu.

16990.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16990.description: Thanks to Po, Hundun opens up his own noodle shop in the village, threatening to put Mr. Ping out of business.

16991.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16991.description: Over Po's objections, Shifu calls in a noble Samurai prawn to help take down a villain from Japan.

16999.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16999.description: Shifu suggests Po takes a vow of silence to help him focus, but his plan goes awry when the panda starts an armed conflict by keeping his mouth shut.

17000.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
17000.description: Once deemed a hero, cobra Fu-xi has turned renegade and is attacking the Valley of Peace. When the villagers adopt an anti-snake sentiment, will Viper help stop Fu-xi...or join him?

17010.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
17010.description: The local thugs love Mr. Ping's soup so much, the noodle shop becomes a villain hangout...with Mr. Ping as their unknowing crime boss!

17011.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
17011.description: Po befriends a group of young (and adorable) orphans-who also happen to be stealing money and goods from the villagers. Will Po be able to reform the kids or fall into the clutches of their evil leader?

23528.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23528.description: Fed up with his constant complaining, Shifu puts lazy Po in charge of training the Furious Five. Things go from bad to worse when the Croc Bandits receive training from a mysterious kung fu master and become the new heroes of the Valley of Peace.

23529.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23529.description: Po is named Head of Imperial Security when klutzy Lu Kang returns to the Valley of Peace as emperor. When an evil menace rises to take over all of China, Po has to turn to some surprising allies in order to save the day.

23553.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23553.description: Po and the Furious Five meet their greatest challenge yet: a supernatural creature who is invincible to the powers of kung fu.

23554.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23554.description: Crane's mom visits the Valley of Peace. Crane reveals to Po that his mom hates Kung Fu so he promised her that he would never have anything to do with it. Crane asks Po and the others to help him keep his secret from his mom.

23560.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23560.description: Po is named Head of Imperial Security when klutzy Lu Kang returns to the Valley of Peace as emperor. When an evil menace rises to take over all of China, Po has to turn to some surprising allies in order to save the day.

23561.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23561.description: When Shifu sends Po to shut down an underground fight club, the panda disobeys his master and joins the club instead.

23569.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23569.description: Po and the Five have to stop a famine by bringing a maniacal gang of food-thieving rats to justice. But, will Po's weakness for food alienate himself from his friends and the very villagers he is trying to help.

23570.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23570.description: Po discovers the seeds of Shuyong: magical items that can actually take the user back in time. After Po disobeys Shifu, evil Fenghuang steals one of the seeds, putting the entire world in danger.

23580.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23580.description: Po's qi is out of balance. He and his friends attempt to re-harmonize the panda using the tradition of musical kung fu. They better work fast, as only Po can stop the destruction of the Eternal Chord and un-creating the universe.

23581.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
23581.description: Po has to help Master Yao after Taotie and Bian Zao steal the Mystic Secrets of Kung Fu right out of the master's head.

29960.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
29960.description: Shifu's evil ex-girlfriend Mei Ling is back...and back together with Shifu! Dubious Po must find out if she is on the level or just using Shifu for her own criminal gain.

29961.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
29961.description: Po and Monkey discover a small village and meet an impostor claiming to be the Dragon Warrior. Po is determined to expose the fraud but could end up doing more harm than good.

29986.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
29986.description: Self-conscious about his size, Mantis ingests a growth potion that makes him huge. Mantis is initially thrilled with the results, but soon his large size puts the entire village and his friends in grave danger.

29987.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
29987.description: With Po and the Furious Five at each other's throats, Shifu takes them all on a disastrous road trip.

29993.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
29993.description: When Po throws a party and invites the First Furious Five to attend, everyone is shocked to learn that Shifu may not be the courageous hero that they thought he was.

29994.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
29994.description: After Bian Zao steals magical lightning powers, he snubs his villain father Taotie and instead teams up with the vicious Tong Fo and the Croc Bandits. Will Po and Taotie knock some sense into Bian Zao before he uses his powers to destroy the village?

30002.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
30002.description: General Tsin is back with a crazy conspiracy theory about alien rice weevils trying to take over the world. When Po learns Tsin is telling the truth, it's up to the Kung Fu Panda to stop the invasion before it's too late.

30003.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
30003.description: After Zeng unhappily quits his job at the Jade Palace, Po cheers up the weepy goose by telling him he could be a kung fu master. Bad idea, Po. Bad idea.

30013.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
30013.description: With his childhood bully back in town, Po must learn to face his fear or risk losing his Dragon Warrior mojo and those that are most important to him.

30014.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
30014.description: Tired of Po getting all the credit and acclaim, the Furious Five quit the Jade Palace and strike out on their own.

36689.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36689.description: It's a battle between master and father when Shifu and Mr. Ping compete for Po's attention and affection during a camping trip. But will their competition get in the way of Po defeating the Valley's newest menace?

36690.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36690.description: After a blow to the head leaves Po with amnesia, Fung and the Croc Bandits are more than happy to use it to their advantage...by convincing the Dragon Warrior that he is their evil bandit leader.

36714.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36714.description: Fung finds an old scroll with instructions for making living terra cotta warriors, and soon it's up to Po and the Five to stop his monstrous clay creation.

36715.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36715.description: When Po is possessed by the ghost of evil Master Ding, it's up to Tigress to save him before Ding can unleash his powers and enslave the Valley of Peace.

36721.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36721.description: Tigress is forced to babysit a small child who has been separated from his parents.

36722.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36722.description: Po and Mantis visit the equivalent of an ancient Chinese Comic-Con, where Po's fanboy enthusiasm gets out of hand.

36730.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36730.description: Po's visit to a famous war hero goes awry when he finds out the retired general is off his rocker.

36731.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36731.description: Po tries to help Crane get his 'mojo' back after Crane is humiliated at a charity event.

36741.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36741.description: When Shifu throws out his back, Po has to sit in as master of the Jade Palace.

36742.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
36742.description: When kung fu is outlawed, Po turns to donning a mask to fight crime.

43361.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43361.description: When two Croc Bandits have a spat, it's up to Po and Mr. Ping to set things right.

43362.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43362.description: In an attempt to get out of training, Po buys some enchanted shoes that will heighten his kung fu abilities. Unfortunately for Po, the magical shoes are evil and will soon put him and all those around him in great danger.

43386.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43386.description: When Tigress discovers she's ill, Po and Monkey set out to obtain the only known cure, which is protected by the evil Scorpion.

43387.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43387.description: After Po accidentally destroys the training hall, he seeks the help of the creator, Taotie, only to discover he's no longer a friend of kung fu... but an enemy!

43393.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43393.description: Po is embarrassed when his dad takes him on a wild goose chase, but it turns out his dad is not so crazy afterall.

43394.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43394.description: When Master Mugan from the Garnet Palace desides she needs a new Kung Fu Master, Tigress volunteers. Will the Furious Five be minus one or will Po convince Tigress to return to the Jade Palace?

43402.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43402.description: When Po's friend Peng returns to the Valley of Peace, everyone is excited...except for Po. What no one else knows is that Peng is actually evil Tai Lung's nephew. Now Po has to admit to powerful Peng that he is the one who skadooshed his uncle.

43403.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43403.description: As the annual Winter Festival approaches, Po doesn't have enough money to buy his dad the present he deserves, so he takes a job as a bounty hunter to capture a dangerous escaped convict for the reward. But Po's plan doesn't go as smooth as he hoped.

43413.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43413.description: Po takes on the challenge of training a lovable but klutzy member of the Emperor's family. However, will Po's training be enough to protect them both from the evil designs of a traitor in their midst?

43414.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
43414.description: After dealing Taotie yet another humiliating defeat, Po is horrified to learn that the villainous warthog has had a full on nervous breakdown. Po is determined to heal his spirit and Taotie is eager to change his evil ways...or is he?

49571.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
49571.description: When Po's fake love letter prank on Monkey backfires, the duo's relationship is put to the test in a story of jealousy, betrayal and, yes, even kidnapping.

Will Shifu and the Five be able to teach Po proper etiquette AND foil the attack of evil Temutai and his army? Not likely.

49596.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
49596.description: When Po is asked to bring a young princess to the King of the Qidan to make a peace offering, they learn that an agreement between the two kingdoms will come at a cost.

49597.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
49597.description: After the Croc Bandits steal Shifu's favorite ruby-encrusted statue of Oogway from Po and Tigress, the two warriors must team up to get the statue back and return it home.

81961.description: Po befriends a group of young (and adorable) orphans-who also happen to be stealing money and goods from the villagers. Will Po be able to reform the kids or fall into the clutches of their evil leader?

81971.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
81971.description: Fed up with his constant complaining, Shifu puts lazy Po in charge of training the Furious Five. Things go from bad to worse when the Croc Bandits receive training from a mysterious kung fu master and become the new heroes of the Valley of Peace.

81972.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
81972.description: Po is named Head of Imperial Security when klutzy Lu Kang returns to the Valley of Peace as emperor. When an evil menace rises to take over all of China, Po has to turn to some surprising allies in order to save the day.

88292.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88292.description: Po is named Head of Imperial Security when klutzy Lu Kang returns to the Valley of Peace as emperor. When an evil menace rises to take over all of China, Po has to turn to some surprising allies in order to save the day.

88293.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88293.description: When Shifu sends Po to shut down an underground fight club, the panda disobeys his master and joins the club instead.

88318.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88318.description: Po discovers his dad, Mr. Ping, is dating Scorpion, but he has trouble trusting his former enemy who claims to no longer be evil.

88319.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88319.description: Po realizes he must select a trophy for the Hall of Heroes, but instead finds himself helping a young villager retrieve a rabbit doll that is much more important than it looks.

88325.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88325.description: Po and the Five have to stop a famine by bringing a maniacal gang of food-thieving rats to justice. But, will Po's weakness for food alienate himself from his friends and the very villagers he is trying to help.

88326.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88326.description: Po discovers the seeds of Shuyong: magical items that can actually take the user back in time. After Po disobeys Shifu, evil Fenghuang steals one of the seeds, putting the entire world in danger.

88334.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88334.description: Po's qi is out of balance. He and his friends attempt to re-harmonize the panda using the tradition of musical kung fu. They better work fast, as only Po can stop the destruction of the Eternal Chord and un-creating the universe.

88335.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88335.description: Po has to help Master Yao after Taotie and Bian Zao steal the Mystic Secrets of Kung Fu right out of the master's head.

88345.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88345.description: Shifu's evil ex-girlfriend Mei Ling is back...and back together with Shifu! Dubious Po must find out if she is on the level or just using Shifu for her own criminal gain.

88346.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
88346.description: Po and Monkey discover a small village and meet an impostor claiming to be the Dragon Warrior. Po is determined to expose the fraud but could end up doing more harm than good.

94168.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94168.description: When Po throws a party and invites the First Furious Five to attend, everyone is shocked to learn that Shifu may not be the courageous hero that they thought he was.

94169.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94169.description: After Bian Zao steals magical lightning powers, he snubs his villain father Taotie and instead teams up with the vicious Tong Fo and the Croc Bandits. Will Po and Taotie knock some sense into Bian Zao before he uses his powers to destroy the village?

94194.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94194.description: Po disguises himself as the merciless villain, Tong Fo, to try and locate a hidden weapon.

94195.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94195.description: When Taotie tries to destroy the Jade Palace and fails, he is sent to prison while his son, Bian Zao, is left behind with Po, who acts like a big brother to the boy who thinks everything is lame!

94201.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94201.description: General Tsin is back with a crazy conspiracy theory about alien rice weevils trying to take over the world. When Po learns Tsin is telling the truth, it's up to the Kung Fu Panda to stop the invasion before it's too late.

94202.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94202.description: After Zeng unhappily quits his job at the Jade Palace, Po cheers up the weepy goose by telling him he could be a kung fu master. Bad idea, Po. Bad idea.

94210.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94210.description: With his childhood bully back in town, Po must learn to face his fear or risk losing his Dragon Warrior mojo and those that are most important to him.

94211.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94211.description: Tired of Po getting all the credit and acclaim, the Furious Five quit the Jade Palace and strike out on their own.

94221.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94221.description: It's a battle between master and father when Shifu and Mr. Ping compete for Po's attention and affection during a camping trip. But will their competition get in the way of Po defeating the Valley's newest menace?

94222.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
94222.description: After a blow to the head leaves Po with amnesia, Fung and the Croc Bandits are more than happy to use it to their advantage...by convincing the Dragon Warrior that he is their evil bandit leader.
